solution.p:
This problem is a direct application of the relation between heat flux and the difference in temperature at two points in a conductor.

	\dfrac{\Delta Q}{A\Delta t} = k\, \dfrac{T_1-T_2}{L}\ \ \ (T_1>T_2).

Here, the following quantities are given:

	 \amp A = 3.14\times 10^{-6}\ \text{m}^2 
	 \amp \Delta t = 30\ \text{min} = 1800\ \text{sec}
	 \amp k = 401\ \text{J/s.m.K}
	 \amp T_1-T_2 = 150\text{K}
	 \amp L = 0.5\  \text{m}



Therefore,

	\Delta Q = k A \Delta t \dfrac{(T_1-T_2)}{L} = 680\ \text{J}.
